    content:
      '<p><a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/julie-rice-phdfoodtechnology/">Dr. Suggs</a><span style="color: rgb(23, 23, 23)"> and </span><a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/allikeigley/">Alli Keigley</a><span style="color: rgb(23, 23, 23)"> wrote in a feature of </span><a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.aiccboxscore.org/2021/03/spring-refresh-with-continuing-education/"><span style="color: rgb(23, 23, 23)">BoxScore by AICC</span></a>, speaking on how spring is the season of hope and calling packaging professionals to prioritize personal growth and continued development through education.</p><p><strong>Dr. Suggs stated</strong>:</p><blockquote><p>Just like the relationships on display everywhere in springtime (bees and flowers, gentle rains and plants), AICC and the Packaging School work together to offer member companies and all respective employees the value-add of training programs. Among these programs are more than 80 online courses in both English and Spanish, all related to the packaging industry and the manufacturing environment.</p><p>What makes our online courses special? For starters, we use a technique called microlearning. If you aren\'t familiar with the term, it just means we take difficult topics, break them up, and arrange them into bite-sized lessons learners can engage with on any device.</p></blockquote><p>Read the full publication here: <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.aiccboxscore.org/2021/03/spring-refresh-with-continuing-education/">https://www.aiccboxscore.org/2021/03/spring-refresh-with-continuing-education/</a></p>',
