    content:
      '<p>Our Founder, <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/drandrewhurley/">Dr. Andrew Hurley</a>, wrote for <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.packworld.com/home/article/21207261/unseen-is-unsold-the-influence-of-product-visibility-on-sales">Packaging World</a> in an article titled, "Unseen is Unsold: The Influence of Product Visibility on Sales."</p><p><strong>Dr. Hurley stated:</strong></p><blockquote><p>Did you know that your product can be invisible (i.e., not purchased) even if it\'s on store shelves?</p><p>How can that be?</p><p>Our research team decided to investigate; the subject was pasta. The group conducted a consumer research project to test the quantitative and qualitative aspects of boxed macaroni and cheese dinners. A total of 227 participants were given a shopping list of five items and asked to shop as they would normally. They were unaware of which item was being studied . . .</p></blockquote><p><span style="color: rgb(23, 23, 23)">Read the full article and results of the study here: </span><a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.packworld.com/home/article/21207261/unseen-is-unsold-the-influence-of-product-visibility-on-sales"><span style="color: rgb(23, 23, 23)">https://www.packworld.com/home/article/21207261/unseen-is-unsold-the-influence-of-product-visibility-on-sales</span></a></p><h3 class="font-bold" style="text-align: start">LEARN MORE ABOUT PACKAGING DESIGN</h3><p style="text-align: start">Here at the Packaging School, we have a collection of online packaging design courses designed <em>by</em> packaging professionals <em>for</em> packaging professionals!</p><p style="text-align: start"><strong>Our suite of packaging design courses include:</strong></p><ul><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://packagingschool.com/courses/packaging-design-workflow">Packaging Design Workflow</a></p></li><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://packagingschool.com/courses/leveraging-human-factors-in-packaging-design">Leveraging Human Factors in Packaging Design</a></p></li><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://packagingschool.com/courses/introduction-to-corrugated-design">Intro to Corrugated Design</a></p></li><li><p><a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://packagingschool.com/courses/package-printing">Package Printing</a></p></li></ul><p style="text-align: start">We also have a collection of packaging design videos on our <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.youtube.com/@Packagingschool">YouTube</a> channel, including our most popular video to date—<a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://youtu.be/euacI5VTBhY?si=vidPR70DR5tIS6my">How Package Design Affects Sales</a>.</p>',
