      '<p>The COVID pandemic shocked the world in many ways . . . but what implications has it had on how food is currently packaged and will any of the changes remain in the future?</p><p>Join us in the <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://youtu.be/x-2THxVyG68?si=0vamJx7z2nub83Ak">YouTube Video</a> above as we interview Professor <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/silvia-d-alesio-6b439659/">Silvia D\'Alesio</a> from Nuova Accademia di Belle Arti (<a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.naba.it/en">NABA</a>) in Milan, Italy to discuss how food packaging is changing in a COVID-19 world.</p><p style="text-align: right">"<em>I\'m reflecting on what packaging can and should be doing to help in this time of crisis</em>."<br>—Silvia D\'Alesio</p>',
