      '<p>Did you know that in 1971 Carolyn Davidson designed the Nike logo for only $35 USD? A logo can make or break a brand. We know a great logo when we see one, but how does one construct a standout logo?</p><p><span style="color: rgb(19, 19, 19)"><strong>Here are 5 tips to consider as you begin your next logo design . . .</strong></span></p><p>1. Make sure you know the message you are trying to convey</p><p>2. Make the design simple</p><p>3. Keep it simple!</p><p>4. Trust that the quality of the person, organization, or service will give your design true meaning</p><p>5. Make sure your logo is easy to reproduce / is versatile</p><p>To learn more about these 5 tips and effective logo design, check out the <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://youtu.be/QSw798xM2sE?si=1c_CmdlxoV-mMhoF">YouTube video</a> linked in the top of this page!</p>',
