      '<p>Have you ever wondered if your used, greasy pizza box can be recycled?</p><p>Many folks are under the impression that something has to be clean and pristine in order to be recycled, but that is not always the case.</p><p>The <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.afandpa.org/news/2023/lets-set-record-straight-pizza-boxes-are-recyclable">American Forest and Paper Association </a>and <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.westrock.com/blog/pizza-box-recycling">WestRock</a> state that used pizza boxes are indeed recyclable. The groups found that grease residue and cheese do not affect the recyclability. This finding has been supported by an array of other associations. <br><br>Learn more about pizza box recycling and packaging at our YouTube channel: <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.youtube.com/@Packagingschool">https://www.youtube.com/@Packagingschool</a></p>',
