      '<p>In this episode of the Packaging School Show, we have a conversation with <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/shannon-anderson-packageinsight/">Shannon Anderson</a> (Client Research Manager, Packaging) of <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://packageinsight.com/">Package InSight</a>. In our talk, we explore their study on the effectiveness of packaging for cereal products.</p><p>Shannon and Package InSight utilized eye-tracking technology to gauge the importance of packaging for cereal. To do so, they had folks wear eye-tracking glasses to look at cereal in plain bags (with no outer packaging) and then cereal in the boxes themselves.</p><p>Read more on the results of the study <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://packageinsight.com/breakfast-cereal/">here</a>! See our full conversation with Shannon in the video embedded above.</p>',
