      '<p>Did you know that automotive parts can have up to 7 different packages throughout their life cycle?</p><p>That\'s a lot of automotive packaging . . .</p><p>Our team wrote in a feature of <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.aiccboxscore.org/2020/03/1-part-7-packages/">BoxScore by AICC</a>, discussing our <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://packagingschool.com/certifications/get-to-know-apc">Automotive Packaging Certificate</a>, annual <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.autopacksummit.com/">Automotive Packaging Summit</a>, and interesting facts about automotive packaging.</p><p><strong>Our team stated</strong>:</p><blockquote><p>Consider that every small part that makes up a vehicle, on average, lives in seven packages throughout its lifespan, and each vehicle is made of ~30,000 parts.</p></blockquote><h3 class="font-bold">Learn More about Automotive Packaging</h3><p>Here at the Packaging School, we have years of experience providing the automotive industry with packaging courses and certificate programs.</p><p>We offer a 100% online Automotive Packaging Certificate; learn more here: <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://packagingschool.com/certifications/get-to-know-apc">https://packagingschool.com/certifications/get-to-know-apc</a>.</p><p>We also have an annual conference focused on connecting OEMs with Tier 1 suppliers called the <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.autopacksummit.com/">Automotive Packaging Summit</a> (APS).</p><p>AutoPack Summit 2024 takes place from October 21 to October 23 in Greenville, SC—learn more here: <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.autopacksummit.com/tickets">https://www.autopacksummit.com/tickets</a>.</p>',
