      '<p>Have you ever heard of the term "sensory marketing"?</p><p>It refers to when brands engage with the five senses to create a connection between their products and their customers. Some people refer to it as "neuromarketing."</p><p>Sensory marketing can be a powerful tool that brands deploy to engage with consumers, especially when applied to the medium of packaging—an already sensory, consumer-facing aspect of a product.</p><p>Join Kevin Keigley as he walks through examples of sensory marketing and its impact on the consumer experience.</p><p>And . . . learn more about how you can incorporate the five senses and ergonomic principles to your packaging systems in our online course <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://packagingschool.com/courses/leveraging-human-factors-in-packaging-design">Leveraging Human Factors in Packaging Design</a>.</p><p>Learn more about packaging at our Youtube channel: <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://www.youtube.com/@Packagingschool">https://www.youtube.com/@Packagingschool</a></p>',
