      '<p><strong>Why is unboxing so popular? </strong><br>In this episode of the Packaging School Show, Episode 24, we take a look at the phenomenon of unboxing videos!<br><br>To do so, we start with our own attempt at unboxing a product we received from <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://neurogum.com/">Nuero</a>. Nuero is a "functional gum &amp; mints" company with a product line enhancing everything from restful sleep to energy and focus. They sent us a box of goods for this video to help us explore the unboxing experience and its impact on consumer perception.</p><p>Nuero\'s box included an informational brochure, a business card, a sticker, two packs of gum, and a pack of energy mints. The components were packaged in a small corrugated box that included Nuero branding.</p><p>The search term "Unboxing" is one of the most popular on YouTube, and part of the appeal of unboxing videos is that they offer us a way to feel part of a celebration, almost like Christmas morning! The unboxing experience is heavily related to the experience of opening a present. It is no longer good enough to ensure the safe delivery of a product, brands must craft an unboxing experience in order to connect with consumers, especially in this eCommerce age. Brands like Nuero are finding ways to meet this consumer expectation.</p><p>Learn more about the phenomenon of "Unboxing" and see other examples of brands who tell a story with their packaging at our <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://youtu.be/jCK0ZvWLRRs?si=sUv1swdakJ9OAaxm">YouTube Channel</a>.</p><p>Learn more about packaging design and it\'s impact on the consumer in our online packaging design courses at <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" href="https://packagingschool.com/all_courses#courses">https://packagingschool.com/all_courses#courses</a></p>',
